div.div: Yasuri Shichika, seventh successor of the Kyotouryuu (bladeless) sword art, lives on an isolated island with his older sister, Nanami. One day Shichika is visited by a woman named Togame, who requests his aid in her quest to find and collect the final twelve swords forged by the legendary master swordsmith, Shikizaki Kiki. Shichika and Togame begin their odyssey by leaving the island he called home for over 20 years. They will face twelve individuals who possess and protect Shikizaki's legendary swords. Join Shichika and Togame on an exciting, epic adventure that defies reality as they discover the true potential of the Kyoutoryuu sword style! (Source: NIS America)
Comedy, Ecchi, Romance, Slice of Life

The protagonist, Naoya, is a first-year in high school. He asks out Saki, a girl he has been in love with, and she agrees to be his girlfriend. He's currently on cloud nine. But then, a beautiful girl named Nagisa comes up to Naoya one day and tells him that she wants to go out with him. Naoya feels himself wavering because Nagisa is such a good girl, and he comes to a decision! A new kind of romcom from a rather unexpected decision is about to begin!
(Source: Crunchyroll)
Ushiro no Seki no Gal ni Sukarete Shimatta. Mou Ore wa Damekamoshirenai

Sandai Fujiwara, a socially bottom-tier boy, sits in front of Shino Yuizaki, a beautiful gal at the top of the social caste.
Physically, they are very close to each other, but with their difference in status, it feels like they live in different worlds, never crossing paths with each other.
Until Sandai found Shino stuck in a ditch, having accidentally slipped.
“Thanks for the shower”
“Well, goodbye then.”
Although he takes Shino home on a whim to let her shower, Sandai remains wary of the gal. However, he finds himself increasingly attracted to Shino, who despite her looks, is actually not that experienced with men, even as she aggressively approaches him.
After some trouble, the two start dating, and begin to spend their days sweetly flirting with each other…….
